# Project Structure

The Madinaty app follows a standard React Native architecture with Expo:

- [App.js](mdc:App.js) - Main app entry point that sets up providers, theme, and navigation
- [index.js](mdc:index.js) - Initial JavaScript file that registers the app component
- [app.json](mdc:app.json) - Expo configuration file
- [config.js](mdc:config.js) - App-wide configuration settings

## Directory Structure:

- `/src` - Main source code directory
  - `/__apis__` - API service calls using axios
  - `/components` - Reusable UI components
  - `/hooks` - Custom React hooks
  - `/locales` - i18n translations (EN and AR languages)
  - `/navigators` - React Navigation setup
  - `/screens` - App screens organized by feature
  - `/stores` - Zustand state management stores
  - `/theme` - Theming configuration

## Key Technologies:
- React Native with Expo
- React Navigation for routing
- i18next for internationalization
- Zustand for state management
- React Native Paper for UI components

